        "summary": "David trusts in the Lord's mercy and rejoices in His salvation.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "How long wilt thou forget me, O Lord? for ever? how long wilt thou hide thy face from me?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Despair.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 121:1 (1\u20132).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having sorrow in my heart daily? how long shall mine enemy be exalted over me?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Suffering.",
                        "start": 49,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Consider and hear me, O Lord my God: lighten mine eyes, lest I sleep the sleep of death;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 55:17 (16\u201318).",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Lest mine enemy say, I have prevailed against him; and those that trouble me rejoice when I am moved.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But I have trusted in thy mercy; my heart shall rejoice in thy salvation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Sam. 2:1 (1\u201310).",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "I will sing unto the Lord, because he hath dealt bountifully with me.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
